                <h1>Understanding the Nervous System: Key Insights</h1>
                <p>The nervous system is a complex network that coordinates body functions and responses to stimuli. It consists of the central nervous system (CNS) — the brain and spinal cord — and the peripheral nervous system (PNS), which includes all other neural elements. It plays a vital role in sensation, movement, cognition, and homeostasis, ensuring all bodily systems work together smoothly.</p>
